      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">A 65-year-old man came to the ophthalmologist with a complaint of gradually increasing blurring of vision in both his eyes since 1 year. After examination, he was diagnosed with bilateral mature senile cataract and was explained how his lenses had lost their transparency leading to blurring of vision. Factors that play significant role in maintaining the outstanding clarity of normal lens are all except:</span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8026646",
